<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,342,1294,1320]" box="[189,342,1294,1320]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1294,1320]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1294,1320]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1341,1404]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Only two populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[515,852,1341,1367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedium" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[515,852,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ameroglossum intermedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[867,966,1342,1368]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are currently known, both in the municipality of Quebrangulo, Agreste mesoregion of 
<collectingRegion box="[815,981,1377,1403]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Alagoas State</collectingRegion>
. Elevation ca 
<specimenCount box="[1145,1227,1377,1404]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1145,1223,1377,1404]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,288,1443,1469]" box="[189,288,1443,1469]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,288,1443,1469]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,288,1443,1469]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1489,1587]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This species occurs exclusively on granite outcrops. Flowering and fruiting recorded in August and like all other 
<taxonomicName box="[347,612,1525,1551]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[347,520,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ameroglossum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
it is pollinated by hummingbirds. The surrounding vegetation was probably originally composed of deciduous forest, but this has now been replaced by natural pasture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,475,1626,1652]" box="[189,475,1626,1652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,475,1626,1652]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,475,1626,1652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Population and threats</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1673,1806]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Only two rock outcrops separated by pasture in a single municipality in 
<collectingRegion box="[1065,1230,1673,1699]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Alagoas State</collectingRegion>
are known to harbour this species. Approximately 
<specimenCount box="[621,731,1708,1734]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="adult">200 adult</specimenCount>
individuals can be found in the first population, whereas the other comprises approximately 30 individuals. The main threat to these populations are farming and grazing of the site by stray animals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,399,1845,1871]" box="[189,399,1845,1871]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,399,1845,1871]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,399,1845,1871]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1400,1892,2024]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Among the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[459,632,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,632,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ameroglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with quadrangular stems, 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[950,1132,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedium" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[950,1132,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. intermedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1140,1232,1892,1918]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
stands out by having reproductive and vegetative structures covered in trichomes, a characteristic otherwise typically observed in 
<taxonomicName box="[340,561,1963,1989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pernambucense">
<emphasis box="[340,561,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. pernambucense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix, 2021" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Wanderley &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Melo &amp; Batista &amp; Felix" authorityYear="2021" box="[704,889,1963,1989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedium" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[704,889,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. intermedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[900,995,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs by having leaves that are principally opposite and decussate, inflorescences of compound dichasia and the revolute lower lip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
